-- Zimbabwe's Inflation Rate Increased to Annual 4.2% in November From 3.6%
-- B y   N e l s o n   B a n y a
-- 2010-12-15T10:16:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-15/zimbabwe-s-inflation-rate-increased-to-annual-4-2-in-november-from-3-6-.html
Zimbabwe’s inflation accelerated to
4.2 percent in November from 3.6 percent in the previous month,
the country’s statistics agency said.  Prices rose 0.5 percent in the month, driven by increases
in the cost of food and beverages, the Harare-based Central
Statistical Office said in a statement handed to reporters
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nelson Gore Banya in Johannesburg at 
 ngbanya@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
